responsibilities_section:
You will be working with modern customer’s platform backed by Azure Cloud services;
You will be supporting our clients in their journey to distributed, one-click delivered environment by developing new solutions or adding new features to already existed ones;
You will be using various configuration tools to provide automation over managing IT infrastructure;
You will be integrating different tools and systems with use of different service accounts;
You will be responsible for monitoring, alerting, diagnostic on tools and also investigating performance degradation/bottlenecks;
You will be working in an Agile environment, which will give your team autonomy to make independent decisions;

requirements_section:
You have at least 4-5 years of experience with Azure Cloud platform;
You know Linux terminal/environment very well;
You can perform regular scripting work with use of Python, Bash, Perl or SQL;
You have experience with continuous integration tools (Azure DevOps, Team City, Jenkins, Gitlab or similar) and continuous delivery/deployment (eg. Octopus);
You know how to use Ansible or Puppet to automate IT infrastructure;
You know how to use Terraform and implement infrastructure as a code approach into your
daily work;
You know how to use Docker, Kubernetes or Open Shift to create containters;
You are proactive communicator with practical solution-oriented mindset able to liaise with
both business-side and IT-side stakeholders.

